      <h1 class="section-heading lbrxt-typescale-d4">LibRext — Typography</h1>

      <p>Back to <a href="./index.html">Specimens</a></p>

      <p>LibRext has a heavy focus on old-style serif fonts, as it looks to early Renaissance printed works as inspiration. The design system’s text styles are organized by "Font Roles" and "Document Roles”</p>

      <p>Font Roles are functional roles that can be shared by multiple elements.</p>

      <p>Document Roles correspond to common document styles and HTML/Markdown structure</p>

      <h2>Typefaces</h2>

      <p>LibRext text styles revolve around six typefaces:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><span class="lbrxt-typescale-4 lbrxt-fontfam-display">Cinzel</span> — Used for display</li>
        <li><span class="lbrxt-typescale-4 lbrxt-fontfam-heading">Cormorant Garamond</span> — Used for headings</li>
        <li><span class="lbrxt-typescale-4 lbrxt-fontfam-body">Crimson Text</span> — Used for body, headings (alt)</li>
        <li><span class="lbrxt-typescale-4 lbrxt-fontfam-label">Open Sans</span> — Used for labels, UI headings</li>
        <li><span class="lbrxt-typescale-4 lbrxt-fontfam-uiBody">Lato</span> — Used for UI body</li>
        <li><span class="lbrxt-typescale-4 lbrxt-fontfam-monospace">Inconsolata</span> — Used for monospace, code</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <section class="page-section">
      <h2>Font Roles</h2>

      <p>Font definitions available for the design system. These are defined by general roles, and can be used by several (more specific) styles.</p>

      <h2>Document Roles</h2>

      <p>
        Font definitions for text within a document. These are defined by specific roles in a page or screen. Such as titles, subtitles, headings, etc.<br />
        The document roles defined in the system include:
      </p>

      <% for(var i=0; i < roles.length; i++) { %>
      <div class="type-role">
        <div class="type-role-specimen">
          <%  if (roles[i].htmlTags[0].length > 0) {
                for(var j=0; j < roles[i].htmlTags.length; j++) {%>
          <<%- roles[i].htmlTags[j].trim() %>>
            <%= roles[i].spec %>
          </<%- roles[i].htmlTags[j].trim() %>><br />
          <% }
        } else { %>
          <span class="<%- roles[i].htmlClass %>">
            <%= roles[i].spec %>
          </span>
          <% } %>
        </div>
        <div class="type-role-info">
          <h4><%= roles[i].name %></h4>
          <span>weight: <%= roles[i].weight %></span><br />
          <span>typescale: <%= roles[i].typescale %></span><br />
          <span>htmlTags: <%= roles[i].htmlTags %></span><br />
          <span>htmlClass: <%= roles[i].htmlClass %></span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <% } %>
    </section>

